## Project Layout

```text
src/{{ package_name }}/     reusable package code
tests/                      pytest tests
tests/fixtures/             shared test fixtures
notebooks/marimo/           exploratory notebook-style work
data/                       raw, interim, processed, external data
models/                     model artefacts
reports/figures/            generated figures
docs/                       project documentation
docs/decisions/             design decision records
examples/                   small runnable examples
scripts/                    developer and maintenance scripts
.github/skills/             project-specific AI coding agent skills
.github/workflows/          GitHub Actions CI
AGENTS.md                   AI assistant coding instructions
pyproject.toml              project metadata and tool configuration
uv.lock                     locked dependencies
```

## Extension Points

This project includes a few empty or documentation-only folders that downstream
teams can build on without changing the base layout:

- Put project documentation in `docs/`.
- Record design decisions in `docs/decisions/`.
- Add small runnable examples in `examples/`.
- Add checked-in developer scripts in `scripts/`.
- Add reusable test fixtures in `tests/fixtures/`.
- Add real AI coding agent skills in `.github/skills/`.

Specialised templates may add extra dependency groups, commands, folders, and
AI assistant rules for their domain. Keep reusable project code in `src/` and
document any domain-specific workflow here.

